<!--
  load-balancer-weighted.xml
  Alternative load-balancer config — WEIGHTED round-robin instead of
  priority/failover. Use for cost-blended routing across PTU + Standard.

  Workshop currently ships load-balancer-priority.xml (priority groups —
  AOAI as P1, SLM as P2 fallback). Real BFSI deployments often need a
  THIRD pattern beyond "primary/secondary":

    Pattern A — Priority groups (load-balancer-priority.xml)
       ▶ "Always use AOAI; fall back to SLM only if AOAI is dead."
       ▶ Right for: production with one strict primary.

    Pattern B — Weighted round-robin (THIS file)
       ▶ "Send 70% to PTU (cheap-per-token), 30% to Standard (burst capacity)."
       ▶ Right for: blended-cost serving where both backends are healthy.

    Pattern C — Session-aware (sticky)
       ▶ "Pin a single conversation to the same backend for the whole
          chat session (so streamed deltas don't get re-routed mid-flight)."
       ▶ Configured on the BACKEND POOL via `sessionAware` attribute, not
          via inline policy. See scripts/apply-apim-policies.sh and the lb-session flag.

  This file shows pattern B. The pool itself is created out-of-band
  (the script does it); this XML simply points the API at the pool.

  Pool composition (created by the script):
    aoai-blended-pool (type=Pool):
      - aoai-ptu-sea     weight=70   (PTU instance, predictable cost)
      - aoai-standard-sea weight=30  (Standard SKU, burst capacity)

  Source:
    https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/api-management/backends#load-balanced-pool
    https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/api-management/genai-gateway-capabilities#load-balancer
-->
<set-backend-service backend-id="aoai-blended-pool" />
